Rails Agent Skills
------------------

The skill definitions under `.munkit/skills/rails-*` and
`.munkit/skills/yard-documentation`, `.munkit/skills/refactor-safely` are
adapted from:

    igmarin/rails-agent-skills
    https://github.com/igmarin/rails-agent-skills
    License:  MIT
    Derived from upstream commit: a255cff5410331ebef355908b303d4fa955d8ba9

Skills adapted in this project:

    rails-code-conventions
    rails-stack-conventions
    rails-migration-safety
    rails-security-review
    rails-architecture-review
    rails-code-review
    rails-review-response
    yard-documentation
    refactor-safely
    rails-bug-triage

Summary of modifications applied to every adapted skill:

  - Test framework references translated from RSpec to Minitest
    (bin/rails test, test/** paths, fixtures).
  - RSpec-only sections removed where no Minitest analogue exists
    (e.g. let / let_it_be / test-prof guidance).
  - Workflow references changed from "PRD → Tasks" to "Munkit spec".
  - Cross-references pruned to the set of skills actually adopted here;
    pointers to non-adopted skills (rspec-best-practices, rails-tdd-slices,
    ruby-service-objects, ruby-api-client-integration, ddd-*,
    rails-engine-*, create-prd, generate-tasks, ticket-planning,
    rails-skills-orchestrator, api-rest-collection, rails-graphql-*,
    strategy-factory-null-calculator) and pointers to upstream sibling
    files (PATTERNS.md, PITFALLS.md, EXAMPLES.md, BOUNDARY_GUIDE.md,
    ADVANCED_TAGS.md, HEURISTICS.md, INTEGRATION.md, REVIEW_CHECKLIST.md)
    have been removed to avoid dangling links.
  - Sections specific to workflows not used here (Jira ticket planning,
    DDD bounded contexts, Rails engines, REST/GraphQL APIs, Serializers,
    APM instrumentation opinions) have been removed or softened.
  - Some code examples have been rewritten in domain terms that match
    this project's epics (materials, training modules, log entries,
    prototypes) instead of the upstream examples (orders, shelters).
  - Auth opinions softened: upstream recommends Devise + Pundit; this
    project has deliberately not chosen an auth library (see Epic 8),
    so guidance refers to "the project's chosen auth approach" without
    prescribing one.

